Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.04,0:00:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte realized that her father and Herr Gabele
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.62,0:00:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,could exchange their ateliers, \Nso she presented this idea to her father.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.62,0:00:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,However, after hearing her out, \Nfather flatly rejected this idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.60,0:00:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Not just that, {lit is "on the contrary" but what he says is not exactly the opposite to what's said before}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.44,0:00:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,he announced his intention \Nof marrying Frau Irene Gerlach.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.01,0:00:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,As if struck by lightning, Lotte had experienced \Na shock strong enough to render her paralyzed.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.21,0:00:33.22,Sign,,0,0,100,,{\c&HEAFCF9&\bord0\blur0.8\fs20}Episode 22 \N {\fs35} Lotte's in Danger!? \N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N {\fs23} \h Translation: Perevodildo | Timings: Sub-RoRo \h
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.22,0:00:37.19,Sign,,0,0,0,,Munich
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.16,0:00:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.13,0:00:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What do I do now, Luise?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.76,0:00:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.08,0:00:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone spoke just now!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.58,0:00:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But I didn't say a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.45,0:01:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That's odd, I could swear...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.25,0:01:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,That must be Editor. \NProbably needs an urgent manuscript. {not sure what she means by "pressing; urging; demanding; demand"}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.60,0:01:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello? Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.26,0:01:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.40,0:01:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,That was odd, they just hang up.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.10,0:01:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a call from Lotte. Must be.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.57,0:01:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Did something happen on her end?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.35,0:01:44.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The thing is... I've been...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.80,0:01:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Feeling a need for a bit of a change in our lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.27,0:01:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.91,0:01:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Once more, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.28,0:01:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So the point is, I've decided to remarry.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.21,0:02:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's with Frau Irene Gerlach.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.48,0:02:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.71,0:02:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What should I do now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.24,0:02:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What to do...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.62,0:02:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... Fraulein, where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.46,0:02:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It's quick.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.89,0:02:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm visiting someone on Cobenzl Boulevard. {avenue; boulevard; tree-lined street, Cobenzlgasse 43 in german ver}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.06,0:02:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, is that so? Take care, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.73,0:03:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And be sure to come home soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.60,0:03:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Cobenzl Boulevard?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.47,0:03:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, I'm pretty sure Young Fraulein \Ndoesn't have friends living in that area.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.54,0:03:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Hans?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.37,0:03:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What's cooking, Luise?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.20,0:03:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Something happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.44,0:03:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You could tell? {I hope she means "is it this obvious from the looks of me?"}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.31,0:03:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that you ask...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.71,0:03:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You really do look mighty troubled. {to think hard; to brood over; to worry too much (about); to torment oneself (with the thought of)}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.80,0:03:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.95,0:03:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Herr Palfy gets married?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.39,0:03:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody but me supposed to know it yet, {I dunno if she means "I'm not supposed to tell anyone" or "it seems nobody knows yet"}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.89,0:03:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,but it seems,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.46,0:04:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,he really does.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.79,0:04:03.55,Sign,,0,0,0,,Cheers, then! {My congratulations}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.55,0:04:05.76,Sign,,0,0,0,,I'm not one bit cheerful about this. {I hate that the english doesn't have a verb sharing root with congratulations and congrats doesn't have a replacement either}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.76,0:04:06.91,Sign,,0,0,0,,Why so?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.91,0:04:08.02,Sign,,0,0,0,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.59,0:04:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Because my mom \Nstill loves dad, even to this day.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.43,0:04:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Your mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.58,0:04:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.97,0:04:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If I were Luise, I would have probably wished \Nfor him to return to your own mom instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.38,0:04:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.42,0:04:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But what matters the most - \Nhow does Herr Palfy himself feel about this? {essential; important; crucial; vital; main}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.72,0:04:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, he... {unsure, maybe he doesn't ask what his feelings are but just asks if they are what decides the matter}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.36,0:04:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The prognosis is grim, isn't it? {forecast; outlook; prospect; prediction}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.16,0:04:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, I want to stop him, at any cost!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.44,0:04:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you think it's futile?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.64,0:04:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, Herr Palfy probably divorced your mom \Nbecause his love for her was gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.64,0:05:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,They say, you sometimes need a break \Neven from the people you love. {I hope she means this, even if I don't know myself what the fuck this means}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.85,0:05:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if we suppose it's so...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.18,0:05:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,For the moment, he certainly loves \Nanother woman, doesn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.66,0:05:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry to break it for you, \Nbut I see no way out.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.06,0:05:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, before, you told me \Nyou don't want to get married again.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.40,0:05:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Herr Palfy is a heartthrob, right? {to be popular (esp. with the opposite sex); to be well liked; to be pampered (spoiled, doted upon, etc.); to be welcomed}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.91,0:05:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,He has the fame, and he has the "handsome."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.98,0:05:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, could you be possibly heading \N to where this dad's lover lives?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.62,0:05:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Hans, why are you asking like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.60,0:05:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So you really do, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.63,0:05:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, I've no way of telling \Nif doing so will bring you good or harm. {unsure what he means: that action; conduct; behaviour; behavior; mobilization; mobilisation good or bad I can't understand}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.16,0:05:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But whatever happens, \NI'm always on your side. {/will support}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.33,0:06:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Hans.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.98,0:06:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, want me to accompany you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.22,0:06:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.07,0:06:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,This ordeal is mine and mine only. \NI'll deal with it myself! {/because it's my problem, I'll do it alone}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.52,0:06:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.76,0:06:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Good bye, Hans.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.56,0:06:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Give it your best, Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.12,0:07:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.52,0:07:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Frau, you have a visitor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.99,0:07:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.63,0:07:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Fraulein Luise Palfy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.83,0:07:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.59,0:08:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,A little girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.03,0:08:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.87,0:08:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So she's here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.40,0:08:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it she wants here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.17,0:08:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. Show her in.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.24,0:08:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.77,0:08:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, in the meantime, make her a cup of cocoa. \NAnd prepare cookies, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.29,0:08:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Will do in a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.78,0:08:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Having ascertained \Nthat Herr Palfy's love for me is genuine,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.39,0:08:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,she decided not to prolong the feud \Nand came here to bury the hatchet, I imagine.{really in doubts with koko ha tatakau yori, might as well be "cocoa atatakau yori" and both make sense here as "rather than fighting this place/my side" or "over some hot cocoa" LMAO}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.49,0:08:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well, then. I will reciprocate \Nyour commendable humility with leniency, {lit would be "then I should adore you too" but I think she means "I'll show some mercy/pity in response"}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.66,0:08:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.96,0:08:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I honestly can't stand the thunderstorms. \NHow about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.94,0:08:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't stand it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.92,0:09:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Pleased to know we have so much in common!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.88,0:09:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, please help yourself to cocoa.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.52,0:09:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You love it, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.59,0:09:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.66,0:09:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's thanks to Herr Palfy telling me oh so much about you, \Nthat I now know you like the back of my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.35,0:09:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only natural, since we're to live as a family \Nfor the rest of our lives! {/together}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.14,0:09:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, it's in my habit to dote on children.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.58,0:09:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm sure, you and me will make the best of fr...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.05,0:09:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It won't happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.55,0:09:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.42,0:09:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason I came here...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.49,0:09:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Pray, don't marry my dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.62,0:10:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Coming, coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.98,0:10:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello! It's Resi, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.12,0:10:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, dear, that's me. \NTo whom do I own the please? {not sure if it's anatasama or donatasama}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.90,0:10:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.98,0:10:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a classmate asking. \NIs Luise home?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.77,0:10:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You're Fraulein's friend?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.34,0:10:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay... She went out some while ago. \NHaven't returned yet, dear. {/she is away from home}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.29,0:10:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.83,0:10:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me, did something happen to Luise lately?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.84,0:10:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Like, she's gotten into trouble?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.44,0:10:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Fraulein got into trouble?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.78,0:10:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,My, what should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.78,0:10:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,A traffic accident or something like that? {added traffic}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.88,0:10:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Calm down! {to become confused (disconcerted, disorganized, disorganised); to be flustered; to panic}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.25,0:10:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just asking if she did! {/I'm the one asking this}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.43,0:10:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, is that all?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.37,0:10:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Weird, where could I have heard this voice before?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.90,0:10:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Gotta go now, have a good day.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.01,0:11:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't seem like she knows anything...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.26,0:11:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,This can't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.66,0:11:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to be a hoax... A joke!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.73,0:11:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Did I hear it quite right? {lit is "please say it to me once again" but what's the point of saying that?}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.16,0:11:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't marry my father, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.33,0:11:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not the one to be joking \Nabout matters so crucial.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.86,0:11:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And why exactly shouldn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.04,0:11:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.58,0:11:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I protest it. {opposition; resistance; antagonism; hostility; objection; dissent​}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.31,0:11:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't let you marry my father!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.78,0:11:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me the reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.02,0:11:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason is my protest!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.27,0:12:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, no protest of yours has any sway \Nover such matters. {/protest all you want, it won't change a thing}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.40,0:12:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,This marriage was Herr Palfy's idea...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.65,0:12:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It was your father, \Nwho had proposed to me of his own accord.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.68,0:12:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you believe, it's in a child's power to override it? {/you, just a child, can stop this?}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.88,0:12:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you've no power to change it yourself, \Nyou came here to ask me to do it? {hope she means this}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.87,0:12:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Herr Palfy's love for me is attested by his own words.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.10,0:12:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, I am the one in position \Nto enforce my will upon you. {really unsure if she means this}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.51,0:12:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Once our marriage is concluded, \Nyou'd be sent to a boarding school, so better start packing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.55,0:13:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That's such a pity. \NI was really hoping we'd start getting along.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.94,0:13:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Farewell.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.65,0:13:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It can't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.35,0:13:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Leave us alone, the way we are now... {unsure, very noisy, maybe she means "me and luise will stay like this" or smt}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.72,0:13:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.00,0:14:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.70,0:14:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,If nothing changes, \Ndad will end up marrying Frau Gerlach!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.97,0:14:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,What can you recommend, Luise?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.11,0:14:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We have decided to convince dad and mom \Nto make up and live together again.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.25,0:14:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.39,0:14:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,All is lost now...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.40,0:14:55.54,Sign,,0,0,0,,Well what do you know - we had but to ask \Nand they sent us all these leftovers. {really unsure what he means, "how about this, if raising (funds, donations, etc.); collection; subscription; solicitation, get sent this much"}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.54,0:14:57.14,Sign,,0,0,0,,Yes, but still...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.61,0:15:00.10,Sign,,0,0,0,,Finding a good cover for Munich Graph among those
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.64,0:15:02.74,Sign,,0,0,0,,is anything but easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.04,0:15:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, who knows is they don't \Nsend over anything good one of this days. {unsure: in the meantime, "this is it" to say is delivered - we don't know"}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.29,0:15:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. Let's wait and hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.05,0:15:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.36,0:15:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, Miss Körner...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.38,0:15:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes? Anything else?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.50,0:15:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,No, nothing... Good job.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.90,0:15:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, then. See you tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.03,0:15:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Turns out, Herr Palfy had been her husband all along.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.81,0:15:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,However... They broke up a long time ago, didn't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.02,0:15:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. That doesn't mean I should desert her as well. {to give up; to abandon (hope, plans); to resign oneself (to)}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.43,0:15:46.43,Sign,,0,0,0,,Seebühl Village
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.43,0:15:49.42,Sign,,0,0,0,,Eipeldauer's Photo Studio {写真館}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.82,0:15:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Munich Graph cover contest? {added}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.63,0:15:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! I know...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.43,0:16:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see, pretty sure I stuck it among those...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.30,0:16:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,No, wait, where else... Did I lose it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.08,0:16:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, here you finally are!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.02,0:16:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the one.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.32,0:16:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You really don't see two twins \Nthat much alike every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.95,0:16:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right! I should send this one \Nto Munich Graph and see what comes out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.74,0:16:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Fraulein!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.34,0:16:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,My, you're burning!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.70,0:16:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! What should I do with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.28,0:16:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Strobl listening.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.62,0:16:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Luise is?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.95,0:16:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,All right! I'll be there in no time!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.92,0:16:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't forget to call Palfy, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.93,0:16:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Concert tonight? \NNonsense! He must be made aware! {/in a middle of concert? doesn't matter, let him know}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.56,0:17:03.20,Sign,,0,0,0,,{il refrigerio } ...For his refreshment,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.20,0:17:05.90,Sign,,0,0,0,,{di poche lacrime } even the few tears 
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.90,0:17:08.54,Sign,,0,0,0,,{gli neghi ancor.} you deny him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.54,0:17:11.11,Sign,,0,0,0,,{ov'è quel barbaro, } Where's that barbarian,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.11,0:17:13.67,Sign,,0,0,0,,{ov'è quel barbaro? } Where's that barbarian?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.67,0:17:16.38,Sign,,0,0,0,,{Le poche lacrime } Who even for our Lord 
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.38,0:17:18.88,Sign,,0,0,0,,{gli neghi ancor - courtesy of alucardnoyuuutsu} denies few tears?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.80,0:17:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Just wait for me, Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.40,0:17:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,As soon as this piece is over, \NI'll hightail home!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.69,0:17:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,39,8 degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.86,0:17:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That much?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.20,0:17:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Could it be that Fraulein has measles again? {in book she never had measles before, but here she adds mada so I think shemeans again}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.30,0:17:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,This has nothing to do with measles.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.18,0:17:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But then... Ah... It's not pneumonia, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.98,0:17:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Not this either.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.28,0:17:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Not this, but what?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.22,0:17:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever it is, \Nwe should first bring down the fever.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.65,0:17:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.46,0:18:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You said something, Fraulein?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.36,0:18:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't do this...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.55,0:18:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Please...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.66,0:18:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What... should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.23,0:18:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll now...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.66,0:18:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Do something! {actually sounds like she is asking herself "what do I do now"}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.41,0:18:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Taxi!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.87,0:18:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I had just barely managed to put her to sleep. {/calm down} {unsure, maybe he means "it's time for us to calm down - calm down? when this is happening?"}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.71,0:18:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Put to sleep? Was it really necessary, doctor? {again unsure, maybe he means "did you have to go this far" or maybe "is this the way she is when put to sleep?"}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.68,0:19:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.05,0:19:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,what wrong with Luise?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.75,0:19:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The more I look at this, the more it seems \Nlike she is experiencing a severe mental shock.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.63,0:19:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,However, it's no run-of-the-mill case.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.73,0:19:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Mental?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.54,0:19:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Shock?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.82,0:19:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Even separated, the twins are connected with a link \Nthat sometimes allows them to share one another's pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.46,0:19:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise's perturbation of the last few days \Nwas entirely justified. {/chest-thumping/uneasiness; vague apprehension; premonition hit the target/was right}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.00,0:19:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,To make matters even worse, {lit is "rude gesture/wrongdoing" so I hope he means "the photographer breached the codex of conduct"}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.16,0:19:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the photo of the girls, \Ntaken during their summer camp trip
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.30,0:20:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is now on its way \Nto the Munich Graph Publishing House.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.34,0:20:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The fate of the two \Nis currently hanging in the balance. {precarious situation; precarious state​}
Comment: 0,0:20:21.27,0:20:21.27,Sign,,0,0,0,,{chapter}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.21,0:20:30.74,Sign,,0,0,0,,A miserable romance {可哀想ね　ロマンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.74,0:20:34.20,Sign,,0,0,0,,A tear-jerking nuance {涙誘うニュアンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.20,0:20:37.92,Sign,,0,0,0,,If you turn another page of your memories, {想い出のページめくれば}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.92,0:20:40.83,Sign,,0,0,0,,Here she is - heroine of the past {追憶のヒロイン} {actually, "the heroine of the recollections" but that doesn't have a nice ring to it}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.05,0:20:52.47,Sign,,0,0,0,,I raise my eyes to your face - {あなたの面影　見上げて咲いている}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.47,0:20:56.23,Sign,,0,0,0,,Suddenly, I'm in full bloom {unsure, maybe "it's flourishing"}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.23,0:20:59.77,Sign,,0,0,0,,A sunflower amidst the blizzard - {act. in the middle of winter}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.77,0:21:03.17,Sign,,0,0,0,,that would be me, my dear {真冬のひまわり　それが私なの}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.61,0:21:06.34,Sign,,0,0,0,,Always on the verge of freezing, {凍えるような気持ちでいつも}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.19,0:21:09.74,Sign,,0,0,0,,My feelings are out of control -
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.74,0:21:14.29,Sign,,0,0,0,,Too stiff to even say "Do you still love me?" {「好き?」と尋くこともできず}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.29,0:21:18.44,Sign,,0,0,0,,My lips just keep wavering in this wind! {風に揺れていたわ}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.99,0:21:23.64,Sign,,0,0,0,,A pitiful Romance {いじらしいね　ロマンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.64,0:21:27.05,Sign,,0,0,0,,Something that only happens in dreams - {夢のような出来事}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.05,0:21:30.68,Sign,,0,0,0,,Trying hard to forget, I fell even more in love {忘れるために愛したの}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.68,0:21:33.45,Sign,,0,0,0,,with heroine of the past {追憶のヒロイン}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.50,0:21:38.27,Sign,,0,0,0,,Miracle that I came across now is hugging me tight {めぐりあえた奇跡　そっと抱きしめて}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.27,0:21:41.68,Sign,,0,0,0,,This is the story of my life, my duty is to protect it! {私だけの歴史　守ってゆくわ}
Comment: 0,0:21:45.27,0:21:45.27,Sign,,0,0,0,,{chapter}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.41,0:21:46.88,Sign,,0,0,0,,Next episode
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.99,0:21:53.72,Sign,,0,0,0,,Lotte, I got something I have to apologize for.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.72,0:21:55.89,Sign,,0,0,0,,It's the same for me, Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.89,0:21:59.39,Sign,,0,0,0,,The secret that we two pledged to guard \Nwas delivered to mom on a silver plate!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.39,0:22:04.59,Sign,,0,0,0,,And on my side, despite my best effort, \NI couldn't do a thing to somehow stop dad from marrying.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.59,0:22:06.46,Sign,,0,0,0,,Who do we do now, Lotte?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.46,0:22:08.56,Sign,,0,0,0,,All is lost now, Luise!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.94,0:22:11.07,Sign,,0,0,0,,Next time, I and Myself:
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.07,0:22:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.91,0:22:15.91,Sign,,0,0,0,,Episode 23 \NSorry, Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.41,0:22:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't miss it!
